author: Written by: Ardan Thornhill
title: Pair sought in French Quarter armed robbery
text:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) - Police are searching for two men connected to an early morning armed robbery in the French Quarter.
The 55-year-old victim told police he was approached by two unknown black men at the corner of N. Rampart and St. Louis around 2:08 a.m. on Oct. 11.
The suspects pulled knives and demanded the victim's wallet, to which the victim complied. They then fled.
Police encourage anyone with information to call CRIMESTOPPERS at 504-822-1111.
